---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

Astro.response.headers.set('Cache-Control', 's-maxage=300, stale-while-revalidate=3600');
---
<Layout
  title="Prompt Builder — Free AI Prompt Builders for ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini & More"
  description="Free prompt builders for ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, Cursor, Bolt, and more. No sign-up required. Describe your task and get a structured AI prompt in seconds."
>
  <div class="px-6 py-12 space-y-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <div class="text-center space-y-3 py-4">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a]">Prompt Builder</h1>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-base max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        A prompt builder takes a plain-language description of what you need from an AI and returns a structured, ready-to-use prompt — with role framing, output format, and context already built in. This site is a collection of free prompt builders for every major AI model. No sign-up. No limits. Works with GPT-4o, ChatGPT-5, Claude, Gemini, Grok, and AI coding tools like Cursor and Bolt. Most people don't need to study prompt engineering — they need a prompt builder that does the work for them.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-3">What Is a Prompt Builder?</h2>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
        A prompt builder is a tool that converts a simple task description into a structured AI prompt. Where you might type "write a product description," a prompt builder returns something like: <em>"You are an experienced copywriter specialising in DTC e-commerce. Write a 100-word product description for [product]. Lead with the primary benefit. Use second-person voice. End with one sentence CTA. Avoid jargon."</em>
      </p>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The difference in output quality is consistent and significant. AI models respond to the structure of the input — vague requests produce generic answers, structured prompts produce responses you can actually use. Prompt builders close the gap between knowing you should write better prompts and actually doing it every time.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">What a Good Prompt Engineering Platform Provides</h2>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Not all prompt builders are equal. The best ones handle all four layers of a well-structured prompt — every tool on this site is built on this principle.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">🎭</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Role framing</p>
            <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Sets the model's expertise and perspective — e.g. "You are a senior product manager at a B2B SaaS company"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">🧩</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Task clarity</p>
            <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Breaks the request into specific, unambiguous steps — e.g. "First outline, then draft, then suggest three headline variants"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">📋</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Output format</p>
            <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Specifies structure, length, and formatting — e.g. "Return as three bullet points, max 20 words each"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">🎯</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Tone &amp; constraints</p>
            <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Calibrates directness, formality, and exclusions — e.g. "Direct tone. Skip caveats. Do not use the word 'leverage'"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6 space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a]">Prompt Builders for Every AI Model</h2>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Different models respond to different prompt structures. Each builder below is tuned for the model it targets — use the one matched to wherever you're working.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-2">ChatGPT Prompt Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          The most-used tool on the site. Generates structured prompts with role framing and format control for GPT-4o and ChatGPT-5. Also includes a prompt improver for existing prompts and an optimizer for iteration.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">ChatGPT Prompt Generator →</a>
          <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-improver" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">ChatGPT Prompt Improver →</a>
          <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-optimizer" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">ChatGPT Prompt Optimizer →</a>
          <a href="/chatgpt-image-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">ChatGPT Image Prompt Generator →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-2">Claude Prompt Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Claude responds to XML-style tags and system prompt structure more precisely than most models. This builder outputs Claude-native format with <code class="bg-[#fdf6e3] px-1 rounded text-xs">&lt;task&gt;</code> and <code class="bg-[#fdf6e3] px-1 rounded text-xs">&lt;instructions&gt;</code> blocks — the patterns that get Claude performing at its ceiling.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <a href="/claude-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">Claude Prompt Generator →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-2">Gemini Prompt Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Built for Google Gemini. Structures prompts with numbered response sections, evidence requirements, and practical examples — the format Gemini follows most precisely. Works with Gemini 2.0 and Gemini Ultra.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <a href="/gemini-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">Gemini Prompt Generator →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-2">Grok Prompt Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Grok is the only mainstream AI with a built-in personality dial. This builder adds directness calibration and optional spicy mode framing — the dimension generic prompt builders completely ignore.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <a href="/grok-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">Grok Prompt Generator →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-2">AI Coding Tool Prompt Builders</h3>
        <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Cursor, Bolt, Lovable, and v0 interpret prompts differently from conversational AI. These builders are tuned for code generation and UI scaffolding — structured for the specific way each tool processes instructions.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <a href="/cursor-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">Cursor Prompt Generator →</a>
          <a href="/bolt-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">Bolt Prompt Generator →</a>
          <a href="/lovable-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">Lovable Prompt Generator →</a>
          <a href="/v0-prompt-generator" class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-lg text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a] hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">v0 Prompt Generator →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">How to Use a Prompt Builder Effectively</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <p><strong class="text-[#1a1a1a]">Be specific before you generate.</strong> "Write an email" produces a weaker generated prompt than "Write a follow-up email to a client who hasn't responded in two weeks — professional tone, 100 words max." The builder structures what you give it. Specific input returns specific prompts.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-[#1a1a1a]">Mention the audience and the format you need.</strong> If you know the response should be a numbered list, a table, or under 200 words, include that in your description. Format constraints are one of the four layers every good prompt includes — giving that information upfront means the generated prompt will already have it baked in.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-[#1a1a1a]">Edit before you paste.</strong> A prompt builder gets you 80% of the way in seconds. The remaining 20% — adding context the tool couldn't know, adjusting for your specific situation — takes 30 seconds and meaningfully improves the output. Don't treat generated prompts as final.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">What is a prompt builder?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">A prompt builder is a free tool that converts a plain-language task description into a structured AI prompt — adding role framing, output format, and tone instructions automatically so you get better results from ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, or Grok without writing the structure yourself.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Are these prompt builders really free?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Yes — all tools on this site are completely free with no sign-up, no account required, and no generation limits. Open the tool, describe your task, generate.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Which prompt builder should I use?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Use the one matched to the model you're prompting. ChatGPT and GPT-4o → <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-generator" class="text-[#1a1a1a] underline hover:no-underline">ChatGPT prompt generator</a>. Claude → <a href="/claude-prompt-generator" class="text-[#1a1a1a] underline hover:no-underline">Claude prompt generator</a>. Gemini → <a href="/gemini-prompt-generator" class="text-[#1a1a1a] underline hover:no-underline">Gemini prompt generator</a>. Grok → <a href="/grok-prompt-generator" class="text-[#1a1a1a] underline hover:no-underline">Grok prompt generator</a>. For coding tools, use the builder for Cursor, Bolt, Lovable, or v0.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Do generated prompts work with ChatGPT-5 and GPT-4o?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Yes. Generated prompts are model-agnostic structured instructions — they work with any model that follows natural language directions. No adjustments needed when switching between GPT-4o, ChatGPT-5, Claude, or Gemini.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">What's the difference between a prompt builder and a prompt engineering platform?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">A prompt engineering platform is the broader category — it includes tools for building, testing, iterating, and managing prompts at scale, often with team features, version control, and analytics. A prompt builder is the entry-level tool in that stack: fast, single-use, no configuration required. If you're an individual or small team, a prompt builder covers most use cases. If you're managing prompts across a product with multiple models and need systematic testing, a full prompt engineering platform like PromptLayer or Langfuse adds the infrastructure layer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-generator" class="block w-full py-4 bg-[#f0b429] border-2 border-[#1c1c1c] rounded-xl text-center font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] text-lg hover:brightness-95 transition-all">
      Start with the ChatGPT Prompt Builder
    </a>

  </div>
</Layout>
